cks   Cadet out of Barracks Cadet in Barracks   Cadet out of Barracks Cadet in Barracks Cadet in Barracks Cadet out of Barracks Cadet out of Barracks Holly Leech  Commandant Office Manager P   540  464 7313 F 540  464 7748 E  leechhc vmi edu Holly Leech      leechhc vmi edu   OC  540 464 7293  OB 135  Evening Night OC 540 464 7962  OB 123  or 540 464 7285   NB 496  Guard Room  540 464 7294  Jackson Arch  Commandant s Office Virginia Military Institute Jackson Arch  Barracks Lexington  VA 24450        Sergeant First Class Christopher Bean SFC Bean joined the United States Army Reserve in January 1992 and graduated from One Station Unit Training at Ft  Sill  OK in June 1992 as a Field Artillery Cannon Crewmember  His first assignment was as a Cannon Crewmember with A Battery  4th Battalion 92nd Field Artillery Regiment  He also served as a Gunner and Assistant Gunner while assigned to A Battery  In 1999  he was assigned to the 1185th Transportation Terminal Brigade as a Military Traffic Management Coordinator  In 2001 he reported to the 1st Battalion 417th Infantry Regiment for reclassification and assignment as a Drill Sergeant  He was deployed to Iraq from March 2004 to March 2005 where he served as NCOIC of a convoy security team  In 2008  SFC Bean served as a Senior Drill Sergeant for G Company 1st Battalion 46th Infantry Regiment at Ft  Knox  KY  In 2009  he served as a Senior Drill Sergeant for E Company  3rd Battalion 60th Infantry Regiment at Ft  Jackson  SC  He then served as a Platoon Sergeant in B Company 1st Battalion 417th Infantry Regiment from 2010 until his retirement in January 2012  His awards and decorations include the Meritorious Service Medal  Army Commendation Medal  Army Achievement Medal  Army Good Conduct Medal  Army Reserve Component Achievement Medal  National Defense Service Medal  Iraqi Campaign Medal  Global War on Terrorism Service Medal  Military Outstanding Volunteer Service Medal  Armed Forces Reserve Medal  Non Commissioned Officers Professional Development Ribbon  Army Service Ribbon  Overseas Service Ribbon  Drill Sergeant Badge  Parachutist Badge  Expert Infantryman Badge and Combat Action Badge  While assigned to the 1185th TTB  he was selected as Brigade NCO of the Year  While assigned to the 1st Battalion 417th Infantry Regiment  he was selected as 98th Division NCO of the Year and Graduated Drill Sergeant School as the Distinguished Honor Graduate      Sergeant First Class Christopher Bean SFC Bean joined the United States Army Reserve in January 1992 and graduated from One Station Unit Training at Ft  Sill  OK in June 1992 as a Field Artillery Cannon Crewmember  His first assignment was as a Cannon Crewmember with A Battery  4th Battalion 92nd Field Artillery Regiment  He also served as a Gunner and Assistant Gunner while assigned to A Battery  In 1999  he was assigned to the 1185th Transportation Terminal Brigade as a Military Traffic Management Coordinator  In 2001 he reported to the 1st Battalion 417th Infantry Regiment for reclassification and assignment as a Drill Sergeant  He was deployed to Iraq from March 2004 to March 2005 where he served as NCOIC of a convoy security team  In 2008  SFC Bean served as a Senior Drill Sergeant for G Company 1st Battalion 46th Infantry Regiment at Ft  Knox  KY  In 2009  he served as a Senior Drill Sergeant for E Company  3rd Battalion 60th Infantry Regiment at Ft  Jackson  SC  He then served as a Platoon Sergeant in B Company 1st Battalion 417th Infantry Regiment from 2010 until his retirement in January 2012  His awards and decorations include the Meritorious Service Medal  Army Commendation Medal  Army Achievement Medal  Army Good Conduct Medal  Army Reserve Component Achievement Medal  National Defense Service Medal  Iraqi Campaign Medal  Global War on Terrorism Service Medal  Military Outstanding Volunteer Service Medal  Armed Forces Reserve Medal  Non Commissioned Officers Professional Development Ribbon  Army Service Ribbon  Overseas Servic